    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-10T12:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-10T12:36:00-05:00" n="1039"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1039">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.918/25.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-10T11:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 10, 1912—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Regarding censorship; Department’s April 9, 7 p.m. The Government’s attitude
                    seems to have been explicitly reported in my April 1, 11 p.m. I have made no
                    categorical and formal inquiry relative to Associated Press or other news
                    agencies, but the President and Mr. Calero have indicated to me their intention
                    not to permit sending of news prejudicial to the Government. Government will
                    probably forbid Associated Press the free exercise of its independence. Please
                    instruct definitely whether or not to make formal representations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
